Package: BrazilMet
Type: Package
Title: The package download and process weather data from automatic weather stations (AWS) of INMET 
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Roberto Filgueiras [aut, cre] (<https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Roberto_Filgueiras>)
Maintainer: The package maintainer <betofilgueiras@gmail.com>
Description: This package is a compilation of function to download and process AWS data from INMET, with the purpose of reference evapotranspiration (ETo) estimation and the estimation of actual evaportranspiration (ETa) based on satellite images.The package aims to make meteorological and agricultural data analisys more parsimonious.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports:
    tidyr,
    stringr,
    readxl,
    dplyr(>= 0.3.0.1),
    extrafont,
    ggplot2
BugReports: https://github.com/FilgueirasR/BrazilMet/issues
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1   
    
